@endnode


@node "peterpan" "Peter Pan"

 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Name:            Peter Pan

 Genre:           Children's

 Hardware needed: 4MB RAM, 256color-screenmode

 Software needed: System 6.07

 Description:     "This revolutionary Story Painting Adventure features the
                  Paintbox Pals, a set of animated paint tools who allow
                  children ages 6 to 10 to control the events in the stories
                  they read. In this adaptation of the classic tale Peter Pan,
                  children help Peter to rescue his friends from the clutches
                  of the evil Captain Hook. With mor than 30 scenes and over
                  250 possible choices, each retelling of Peter Pan is unique
                  - limited only by a child's imagination." - Electronic Arts

 Tested on:       A4000, Cyberstorm040/40MHz, Kick/WB3.0, Cybervision64,
                  A2091-SCSI-Controller, Toshiba XM3801B-SCSI-CD-ROM drive,
                  22MB RAM (10MB assigned to Shapeshifter), MacOS 7.5.5,

 Rating:          Works even on 030/25MHz/Cybervision64/16MB RAM
                  I'm not a child anymore...so I don't know if it is really
                  interesting...

 Demo available:  Maybe at: http://www.ea.com

 <Tested by: Andreas.Etzrodt@eure.de>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

@endnode


