@node "junglebook" "The Jungle Book"

 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Name:            The Jungle Book

 Genre:           Children's

 Hardware needed: 2MB RAM, 256color-screenmode, Single-Speed CD-ROM,

 Software needed: System 6.07

 Description:     "Kids unite with the Paintbox Pals (TM) to help `direct`
                  events in this wonderful classic tal. Join Mowgli in his
                  adventures throughout the mysterious Indian jungle.
                  Travel the jungle with Baloo and Begheera, and help Mowgli
                  fend off the dastardly tiger, Shere Khan. Kipling's tale
                  unfolds according to the choices your child makes with the
                  mogical Paintbox Pals, who enable Kids to affect each scene
                  of the story by choosing from hundreds of possible outcomes.
                  - Electronic Arts

 Tested on:       A4000, Cyberstorm040/40MHz, Kick/WB3.0, Cybervision64,
                  A2091-SCSI-Controller, Toshiba XM3801B-SCSI-CD-ROM drive,
                  22MB RAM (10MB assigned to Shapeshifter), MacOS 7.5.5,

 Rating:          Works even on 030/25MHz/Cybervision64/16MB RAM
                  I'm not a child anymore...so I don't know if it is really
                  interesting...

